UID:b3e1fcbb28fb6e59b754772745be6896@mdh
DTSTAMP:20260613T123010Z
DTSTART:20260614T223000Z
DTEND:20260614T232000Z
SUMMARY:🏒 Stick & Puck – Sylvania\, OH
DESCRIPTION:This is an 8-week instructional program for persons ages 18 &amp\; older that want to learn the basics of skating and hockey. It is recommended that participants have been on ice skates before classes begin. USA HOCKEY MEMBERSHIP IS REQUIRED TO PARTCIPATE (membership.usahockey.com). Partial equipment is required (skates\, helmet\, face mask\, shin guards\, elbow pads\, hockey gloves\, and stick). Hockey pants and shoulder pads are not required but recommended. A<span style="white-space-collapse: preserve\;"> blank practice jersey included. T</span>his program will assist players that would eventually like to join the Adult D-League for new and developing players.&nbsp\;\nRink: Tam-O-Shanter Ice Rink – Sylvania\, OH\n~58 mi from Ann Arbor\nPrice: $10\nSource: DaySmart\nInfo: https://apps.daysmartrecreation.com/dash/x/#/online/tamoshanter/event-registration\nConfirm with rink — schedule subject to change.
LOCATION:Tam-O-Shanter Ice Rink – Sylvania\, OH
URL:https://apps.daysmartrecreation.com/dash/x/#/online/tamoshanter/event-registration
END:VEVENT
